On Sat, 27 Feb 1999, Wai-Sun Chia wrote:
> My problem is that for the Alpha squids, ping time on the local subnet
> increases with time. i.e. network throughput slowly but surely
> decreases; from a ping RTT of 3ms to 3000ms from another PC on the same
> subnet. This 1000 fold degradation typically takes from a couple of
> hours to maybe a day depends on traffic. After which the alpha boxes are
> totally inaccessible either via ftp or telnet. This sucks because one of
> them is my main ftp server!
I have seen this problem on ix86, it and other tulip issues were solved for
me by upgrading to the latest tulip driver; currently v.90q iirc.
